  "texts": [
    "We note the excellent overlap between the two surveys, whereby only relatively small areas at the extreme edges of the northern and southern patches are without complete (ZYJHK s) information.Initial VIKING observations were taken between 13 November 2009 and 24 August 2016, defining the final footprint.",
    "Subsequently, some observations were repeated (primarily of data with instrumental problems), with the final observation dating from 16 February 2018.",
    "The data rate of observations is shown in Fig. 19.",
    "All VIKING observations can be found in the ESO archive under programme ID 179.A-2004, and a summary of the observational requirements is provided in Table 8.",
    "A detailed description of the survey design and observing strategy is given in Edge et al. (2013) and Venemans et al."
  ]
}